events.name: Front End TL;DR May 2015
events.description: Paypal Singapore is graciously hosting the front end developer community. Join to find out what they've been up to on the front end side, as well as to share and learn any front end technology you're interested in. Pizza and drinks will be provided. Address: 5 Temasek Boulevard, Level 9, Suntec Tower 5, Singapore 038985 FEDS is about hands-on, collaborative learning. Join the session if you'd like to learn new front end technology. Schedule: Every third Monday of the month. Different venue each time. 7:00pm — Arrival, registration, seating 7:10pm — Intro talk 7:30pm — Teams work on mini challenges 8:30pm — Presentations, awards 9:00pm — The end. More info: http://feds.strikingly.com/ PS: Bring a laptop and show up a bit earlier to get set up on the wifi.

events.name: iOS Dev Scout May Meetup
events.description: Venue: PlugIn@BLK71 71 Ayer Rajah Crescent, #02-18, Singapore[masked] Nearby MRT: One North Agenda: 7:00PM: 1st Session on Core Plot - iOS Graph Library by Shubham Goyal & Rameez Remsudeen https://github.com/core-plot/core-plot 7:45PM: Gesture like the Tinder app by Aizat Omar Reference to Tinder: https://itunes.apple.com/sg/app/tinder/id547702041?mt=8 8:15PM: Show & Tell - We've 3 guys interested in show and tell session this month. These will be short and quick demos of apps you have been working on.

events.name: WordPress Meetup (May 2015)
events.description: * Please fill out our survey here, if you haven't done so! https://sgwp.wufoo.com/forms/wordpress-singapore-meetup-survey/ It's time for another meetup! The WordPress Singapore meetup aims to bring together people of all skill levels, from beginners to people who have been using WordPress since it was first released in 2003 (woah!). We're having an open discussion and meet-and-greet this month, with topics that range from: - Core and plugin updates - Choosing great plugins - Speeding up your WordPress site - Securing your servers What we'll share about that night depends on what you wish to learn! We've also just come under the WordPress Foundation, so we'll also be thinking through how future meetups will be held, and looking for volunteers to help run future meetups. Feel free to also RSVP on our Meetup group: http://www.meetup.com/WordPress-Singapore/events/222475151/
